          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px; 
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">US-Russia talks in Riyadh</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ukraine-war-talks-begin-riyadh-lavrov-rubio-meeting.png" alt="Talks to end the war in Ukraine began in Riyadh with a meeting between Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov and US Secretary of State Marco Rubio" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Talks to end the war in Ukraine began in Riyadh with a meeting between Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov and US Secretary of State Marco Rubio. Credits: The National News</p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The US and Russia held their first talk on ending the war in Ukraine and <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-19-02-2025-h1-1-improving-diplomatic-and-economic-ties?source=website" target="_blank">improving diplomatic and economic ties</a> in Saudi Arabia’s capital, Riyadh. This marks a major shift under President Trump's administration and US foreign policy. Marco Rubio and Russian FM Sergey Lavrov agreed to restore embassy staffing, support Ukraine peace talks, and explore economic cooperation.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">However, Ukraine and European allies are worried about being sidelined, as no Ukrainian officials were present or invited. Volodymyr Zelenskyy said his country would not accept any outcome from the talks. The US hinted that Ukraine may have to make territorial concessions, which sparked even more concern. Meanwhile, Russia continues its assault on Ukraine, launching 176 drones overnight, with strikes injuring civilians.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
